Unlike many other biblical characters who argue with God (like Moses or Jonah), Balaam followed God's rules to the letter. When King Balak offered him mountains of gold to curse Israel, Balaam repeatedly said: "Even if Balak gave me his house full of silver and gold, I could not do anything small or great to go beyond the command of the Lord my God" (Numbers 22:18). He refused to act without divine permission.
